    "html": "<section class=\"problem\" id=\"6-107\">\n<h2>6-107</h2>\n<div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Lesson</span> Sorted to Unit 7, Section 5: Exponential Modeling</div>\n<div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Compares linear and exponential models for decay data using scatterplots, regressions, and residual plots.</div>\n<div><div><div class=\"row\"><div class=\"col-sm-9\"><p>Recall that Giulia’s father uses dry ice to keep the glasses in his restaurant very cold. The dry ice sublimates in the restaurant cooler as shown in the table at right. </p><ol class=\"lower-alpha\" type=\"a\"><li><p>Recreate the scatterplot and the LSRL of this data on your calculator or use the <a class=\"etool-link\" href=\"https://www.desmos.com/calculator/lrfvn1zcco\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">6-107 Student eTool</a>. Click in the lower right corner of the graph to view it in full-screen mode.Sketch the residual plot.  What does the residual plot tell you about the original data Giulia collected? \t\t</p></li><li><p>What type of function might fit this data better?   </p></li></ol></div><div class=\"col-sm-3\"><table><tbody><tr><th><p># hours<br/> \t\t\t\tafter<br/> \t\t\t\tnoon</p></th><th><p>Weight<br/> \t\t\t\tof dry<br/> \t\t\t\tice (oz)</p></th></tr><tr><td><p>$0$</p></td><td><p>$15.3$</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>$1$</p></td><td><p>$14.7$</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>$2$</p></td><td><p>$14.3$</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>$3$</p></td><td><p>$13.6$</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>$4$</p></td><td><p>$13.1$</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>$5$</p></td><td><p>$12.5$</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>$6$</p></td><td><p>$11.9$</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>$7$</p></td><td><p>$11.5$</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>$8$</p></td><td><p>$11.0$</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>$9$</p></td><td><p>$10.6$</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>$10$</p></td><td><p>$10.2$</p></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div><ol class=\"lower-alpha\" start=\"3\" type=\"a\"><li><p>Use your calculator to find the exponential regression equation. Add this graph to the scatterplot sketch. Be sure to label the graph with the equation.  </p></li></ol><div class=\"row\"><div class=\"col-sm-9\"><ol class=\"lower-alpha\" start=\"4\" type=\"a\"><li><p>Based on the scatterplot alone, does the linear model or the exponential model fit the data better?</p></li><li><p>Make a residual plot of the exponential regression. Comment on the appropriateness of the exponential model.</p></li></ol></div><div class=\"col-sm-3 col-align-top\"><p></p></div></div></div><p><img alt=\"Figure for 6-107\" class=\"figure-img\" src=\"assets/6-107.png\"/></p></div>\n</section>",
