    "html": "<section class=\"problem\" id=\"7-69\">\n<h2>7-69</h2>\n<div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Lesson</span> Sorted to Unit 7, Section 5: Exponential Modeling</div>\n<div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Writes and uses an exponential model from a contextual graph, then evaluates interpolation, extrapolation, and model accuracy.</div>\n<div class=\"row\"><div>\n<p>GRAPH → EQUATION</p>\n<p>Suppose the annual fees for attending a public university were \\$7000 in 2010 and the annual cost can be seen in the graph at right. Note that <em>x</em> represents the number of years after 2010.</p>\n<ol class=\"lower-alpha\" type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Write an equation to describe this situation.</p></li>\n<li><p>Use this model to predict the cost of attending a public university in the first year you would be eligible to enroll.</p></li>\n<li><p>What was the cost in 2000, assuming the rate of increase was the same during the time period from 2000 to 2010?</p></li>\n<li><p>Are you confident with your prediction in part (c)? Explain.</p></li>\n<li><p>In 2012 the annual cost was actually \\$8244. How accurate was the model? What actually happened?</p></li>\n</ol>\n</div><div><img alt=\"Captured exponential graph for 7-69.\" class=\"figure-img\" src=\"assets/7-69.png\"/></div></div>\n</section>",
