    "html": "<article class=\"problem\" id=\"7-103\">\n<h3>7-103.</h3>\n<div class=\"meta\"><span class=\"tag\">Lesson</span><span>Sorted to Unit 7, Section 5: Exponential Modeling</span></div>\n<div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Builds tables, graphs, equations, and comparisons for depreciation/appreciation models.</div>\n<p>Investigate the changing values of each of the cars by addressing the questions below.</p>\n<ol class=\"lower-alpha\">\n<li>What is the multiplier for the Concord? For the Escalate? For the Rustang?</li>\n<li>Make a table like the one below and calculate the value for each car for each year shown.\n        <table>\n<tr><th>Year</th><th>Concord</th><th>Escalate</th><th>Rustang</th></tr>\n<tr><td>$0$</td><td>$\\$27{,}000$</td><td>$\\$39{,}000$</td><td>$\\$15{,}000$</td></tr>\n<tr><td>$1$</td><td>$\\$25{,}380$</td><td>$\\$30{,}225$</td><td class=\"blank\"> </td></tr>\n<tr><td>$2$</td><td class=\"blank\"> </td><td class=\"blank\"> </td><td class=\"blank\"> </td></tr>\n<tr><td>$3$</td><td class=\"blank\"> </td><td class=\"blank\"> </td><td class=\"blank\"> </td></tr>\n<tr><td>$4$</td><td class=\"blank\"> </td><td class=\"blank\"> </td><td class=\"blank\"> </td></tr>\n<tr><td>$5$</td><td class=\"blank\"> </td><td class=\"blank\"> </td><td class=\"blank\"> </td></tr>\n<tr><td>$\\ldots$</td><td class=\"blank\"> </td><td class=\"blank\"> </td><td class=\"blank\"> </td></tr>\n<tr><td>$10$</td><td class=\"blank\"> </td><td class=\"blank\"> </td><td class=\"blank\"> </td></tr>\n<tr><td>$\\ldots$</td><td class=\"blank\"> </td><td class=\"blank\"> </td><td class=\"blank\"> </td></tr>\n<tr><td>$n$</td><td class=\"blank\"> </td><td class=\"blank\"> </td><td class=\"blank\"> </td></tr>\n</table>\n</li>\n<li>On your own graph paper, graph the data for all three cars on the same set of axes. Are the graphs linear? How are they similar? How are they different? You may want to use a different color for each car.</li>\n<li>Write a function to represent the value of each car.</li>\n<li>What were the values of the Concord and the Escalate when they were new? How much value, in dollars, did each car lose from $2010$ to $2012$?</li>\n<li>Using the graph, which of the three cars is worth the most after one year? After $3$ years? After $10$ years? In how many years will the values of the Concord and Escalate be the same?</li>\n<li>Pick one of the three cars and explain why Jeralyn should buy it. Has this problem changed your view of buying cars?</li>\n</ol>\n</article>",
