    "html": "<section class=\"problem\" id=\"11-52\">\n<h2>11-52</h2>\n<div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Review/Preview</span> Sorted to Unit 7, Section 5: Exponential Modeling</div>\n<div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Interprets parameters in an exponential decay model with a horizontal asymptote in context.</div>\n<p>The function $f(x)=140(0.7)^x+72$, where $x$ is the time in minutes, could represent the temperature over time of a hot cup of tea placed on the kitchen counter. What does the $72$ represent in the context of this situation? What does the $0.7$ represent?</p>\n</section>",
